<p>I have 2 UIView of the same size, with this constraints:</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/wrxeG.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/wrxeG.png" alt="enter image description here"></a> A: <a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/rHMTl.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/rHMTl.png" alt="enter image description here"></a> B: <a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/UAL6W.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/UAL6W.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>These two UIViews are draggable and when the first comes out, the second UIView takes his place, in a loop:</p>  <p>I tried with different solutions, like this: At start, the UIViews are correct:</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/o0Oqx.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/o0Oqx.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>but after the swipe, the second UIView is not correct:</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/QanUO.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/QanUO.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>or this: At start the central UIView is correct but the second there isn't:</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/dhe9b.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/dhe9b.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>after the swipe, the second one enters correctly, but the old one  returns in the wrong position (in this example I set the position at center of the view, normally it should return to the right).</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/vj0ab.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/vj0ab.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>Code:</p>  <pre><code>[_cardViewA setTranslatesAutoresizingMaskIntoConstraints:NO];      [self.view addConstraint:[NSLayoutConstraint constraintWithItem:_cardViewA                                                           attribute:NSLayoutAttributeHeight                                                     